In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 2 through March 8, 2014, as National Consumer Protection Week. He emphasizes the importance of strong consumer protections in order to ensure a fair marketplace and a thriving economy. The President highlights the actions his administration has taken to expose deceptive mortgage schemes, crack down on abusive debt collection practices, and prevent illegal market rigging. He also mentions the passing of the strongest consumer financial protection law in history and the creation of an independent watchdog for the financial world. The President stresses the need for Americans to be aware of their rights and have the tools to make informed decisions in the open market. He encourages government officials, industry leaders, and advocates to share information about consumer protection and educate citizens about their rights. Overall, the President calls for an economy that works for everyone and allows every American to pursue their own happiness.